			anything capable of supporting them, either through general
			poverty, or simply because they are the fifth or sixth son.
			Such nobles face a choice of going into the church, or
			becoming a wandering knight, looking for employment, fame
			and fortune.
			</para>
			<para>
			Such knights do not see themselves as mercenaries, though
			the road they take is very similar to that profession. They
			believe they fight for ideals, though cash in hand, a warm
			meal and a roof over their head will do in a pinch.
